
THIS DOES NOT WORK!!!

- it looks like port 5 is an internal port (aka wireless) and port 0 is the 
  wan port

- the switch is vlan 0 and the wan/internal is vlan 1

http://forum.openwrt.org/viewtopic.php?id=2711

- ssh in

- pull port 4 off vlan 0

nvram set vlan0ports="1 2 3 5*"

- set up the new vlan

nvram set vlan2hwname="et0"
nvram set vlan2ports="4 5"

- add it to the list of lans

nvram set script_fire="brctl addbr br1
brctl addif br1 eth0
brctl addif br1 vlan2
brctl stp br1 0
ifconfig br1 192.168.42.254 netmask 255.255.255.0
"

nvram commit





- reboot

